25/03/2003
PARIS, France -- Foreign Minister Dominique de Villepin pledged on Monday (24 March) his government's support of Bulgaria's EU integration efforts. In a letter to Bulgaria's Ambassador to France Marin Raykov, de Villepin praised the development of relations between the two countries. He also expressed his commitment to promote co-operation and harmonisation of two countries' positions in the light of international events.
Meanwhile, a delegation from Bulgaria's Defence Ministry went to Moscow and reached a deal to establish a joint venture with the Russian aircraft corporation MiG to repair aircraft and produce parts. Details are to be finalised next month. (Dnevnik, Pari, Trud - 25/03/03; BTA, Mediapool - 24/03/03)
